Note on the Apache/AGPL boundary
--------------------------------
hippmem-core, hippmem-model, and hippmem-store are Apache-2.0 and
can be used standalone in any project. However, once you link any
of them into the same binary or service as an AGPL-3.0-only crate
(hippmem-write, -retrieval, -consolidation, -engine, -grpc, -eval),
the combined work becomes subject to AGPL-3.0-only. The Apache
crates never depend on the AGPL crates, so the permissive license
only applies when they are used in isolation.

